        <div type="docbody">
          <opener>
            <dateline>Boston April 1 1893</dateline>
            <salute>My dear Mr Atkinson</salute>
          </opener>
          <p> Please send a good pail over or bucket or both (we have one at the kitchen of the older sort) to 
            Miss <persRef ref="davis-katherine">Katherine B Davis</persRef> 80 Willoughby Street Brooklyn N.Y.
Miss Davis is to personate a workingman's wife who has four children to care for &amp; whose husband earns about 450 a year.</p>
<p>She wishes to experiment
<pb n="2"/>
in hours out of school these next two months &amp; she wishes to use the things which such a woman could have. This can be put on my account if you like.</p>

          <closer>Very truly <lb/>
<signed>Ellen H. Richards</signed></closer>
        </div>
